==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: ham-handed
<hw>ham-handed</hw></mhw> <pos>adj.</pos>
<def>not skillful in physical movement especially with the hands;
clumsy; bungling; -- also used metaphorically of actions; <as>as,
<ex>ham-handed</ex> governmental interference</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> bumbling, bungling, butterfingered, handless,
heavy-handed, left-handed.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hamiform</ent>⟦br⟧
